subSubSection.paragraph:
The type locality (arrow in map of
figure 1
) at 5 0+ m shows a complex habitat of a mixed reef and sandy habitat [ 29 , 30 ]. Two paratypes were collected from the continental shelf near Perth ( 72 m , circle in
figure 1
); the habitat at this site is unknown. The fourth paratype , collected at Cottesloe, Perth, does not have depth data, as it was washed up on the beach.
